{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"title":"Dough","content":["Lightly grease a large bowl and set aside. Line 2 pizza pans with parchment.","Place bread flour, whole wheat flour, water, sugar, yeast, 1 oz olive oil and salt into mixing bowl and knead <nobr>2 min\/<\/nobr>.","Form dough into a ball and transfer into prepared bowl. Cover with cling wrap and let dough rise until doubled in size (approx. 1 hr.).","Preheat oven to 450°F. Divide dough in half and place onto prepared pans. Stretch dough out to pan edges, with lightly floured fingers. Cover with clean kitchen towels and let rise 5 minutes."]},{"title":"Filling","content":["Place sugar and lemon peel into mixing bowl and zest <nobr>15 sec\/speed 9<\/nobr>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula.","Add mascarpone and lemon juice and mix <nobr>15 sec\/speed 4<\/nobr>. Set aside.","Brush each pizza base with 0.5 oz butter and sprinkle each with 1 tbsp turbinado sugar. Bake for 5 minutes (450°F). Divide reserved lemon mascarpone and carefully spread onto each half-baked pizza. Sprinkle each with 6 oz blueberries and bake a further 5-7 minutes, until the blueberries burst open. Serve warm."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"Dough","content":["1 oz olive oil, plus extra to grease","15 oz bread flour","2 ½ oz whole wheat flour","9 oz warm water (100°F-110°F)","½ oz sugar","2 ¼ tsp rapid rise yeast","2 tsp salt"]},{"title":"Filling","content":["2 oz sugar","1 lemon, thin peel only, no pith","8 oz mascarpone","1 tbsp freshly squeezed lemon juice","1 oz salted butter, room temperature, divided","2 tbsp turbinado sugar, divided","12 oz fresh blueberries, divided"]}],"id":"r170723","imageLink":"https:\/\/1.bp.blogspot.com\/-rzbv7Gmye0E\/XZWrNQawF9I\/AAAAAAAAfj4\/fQRuUP1VoCIwrZoOi96rfvgXqYC1hISJQCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_fSxAmCtnJgnRy6Wk.png","title":"Blueberry and Lemon Mascarpone Dessert Pizza","publishedAt":"2017-05-12T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"40 g","fat":"70 g","uom":"per 1 pieces","carbohydrates":"260 